---
import SubpageLayout from '@/layouts/SubpageLayout.astro';
import Section from '@/components/layout/Section.astro';
---

<SubpageLayout title="Privacy Policy | ralph by Beneficious">
  <main>
    <Section background="primary" spacing="xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-primary mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-8">Last updated: June 26, 2025</p>

        <div class="space-y-12">
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Overview
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              At Beneficious ("we," "our," or "us"), we take your privacy seriously. Ralph is
              designed with a unique deployment model that ensures your data never leaves your
              control. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information in connection with
              Ralph and our services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Our Privacy-First Architecture
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Ralph operates on a fundamentally different model than typical SaaS platforms:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>Ralph runs entirely on your own infrastructure</li>
              <li>Your data never leaves your servers or cloud environment</li>
              <li>
                We have no access to your deal information, portfolio data, or any proprietary
                information
              </li>
              <li>Think of Ralph as software you install, not a service you send data to</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Information We Collect
            </h2>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Personal Information</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We may collect the following types of personal information:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Contact Information:</strong> First name, last name, email address, phone number,
                company name, job title
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Account Information:</strong> Username, password, and account preferences
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Communication Records:</strong> Support tickets, feedback, and correspondence
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Professional Information:</strong> Company details and role-specific information
                for service customization
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Technical Information</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We automatically collect certain technical information:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Usage Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, device identifiers, operating
                system
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Website Analytics:</strong> Pages visited, time spent, referral sources (marketing
                website only)
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Technical Logs:</strong> Error reports and system performance data (when shared
                voluntarily)
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">
              What We Absolutely Do NOT Collect
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>
                <strong>Business Data:</strong> We never collect, store, or access your deal information,
                portfolio data, or proprietary business information
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Usage Analytics from Ralph:</strong> No tracking or analytics within the Ralph
                application itself
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Training Data:</strong> We never use your data to train or improve our AI models
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Cross-Client Data:</strong> We never share or combine data between different
                client deployments
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Security & Compliance
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We implement commercially reasonable technical, administrative, and organizational
              measures to protect your information from loss, misuse, and unauthorized access:
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">
              Enterprise Security Architecture
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Infrastructure Security:</strong> Ralph inherits and extends your organization's
                existing security standards
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Authentication Integration:</strong> Full support for SAML/SSO, identity providers,
                and multi-factor authentication
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Monitoring & Compliance:</strong> Compatible with your SIEM tools, audit logging,
                and compliance frameworks
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Air-Gapped Support:</strong> Deployable in completely isolated environments with
                no external connectivity
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Data Governance:</strong> Respects and enforces your existing data governance
                policies and procedures
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">
              Security Certifications & Standards
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>SOC 2 Compliance:</strong> We are actively pursuing SOC 2 Type I and Type II
                certifications
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Industry Standards:</strong> Built to support various compliance requirements
                including GDPR, CCPA, and financial regulations
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Secure Development:</strong> Regular code audits, penetration testing, and encrypted
                communications
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Third-Party Assessments:</strong> Independent security reviews and vulnerability
                assessments
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Data Protection</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              <strong>Important:</strong> While we implement robust security measures for any data we
              handle, remember that with Ralph's architecture, your sensitive business data never leaves
              your controlled environment. You maintain complete control over:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>All security configurations and access controls</li>
              <li>Data encryption, backup, and disaster recovery procedures</li>
              <li>User permissions and audit trail management</li>
              <li>Compliance with your industry-specific regulations</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              LP and Confidential Information
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Limited Partner (LP) information and all confidential data are treated with the
              highest level of security:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>Access permissions are fully configurable by your team</li>
              <li>Role-based access controls match your firm's existing permissions</li>
              <li>Complete audit trails of all agent activities</li>
              <li>Data segregation between portfolio companies is maintained</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Cookies and Tracking Technologies
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We use cookies and similar tracking technologies on our marketing website to improve
              your experience:
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for website functionality, user authentication,
                and fraud prevention. These cannot be disabled.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> Remember your preferences, login details, and language
                settings
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand website traffic and usage patterns
                (with your consent)
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Cookie Policy Acceptance:</strong> Track whether you've accepted our cookie usage
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Cookie Management</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              You can control cookie settings through your browser preferences. However, disabling
              essential cookies may affect website functionality.
            </p>

            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              <strong>Important:</strong> No tracking cookies or analytics are used within the Ralph
              application itself - only on this marketing website.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Data Retention
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Since Ralph operates on your infrastructure:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>You control all data retention policies</li>
              <li>Data deletion is managed according to your organization's policies</li>
              <li>We retain only minimal contact information for business relationships</li>
              <li>Support communications are retained only as long as necessary</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Your Data Rights
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              You have the following rights regarding your personal information:
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Access and Control Rights</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Right to Access:</strong> Request information about what personal data we have
                about you
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Right to Correct:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal
                information
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Right to Delete:</strong> Request deletion of your personal information (subject
                to legal retention requirements)
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Right to Withdraw Consent:</strong> Withdraw consent for data processing where
                consent is the legal basis
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> Request your data in a structured, commonly
                used format
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Communication Preferences</h3>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Marketing Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe from marketing communications at any
                time
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Communication Preferences:</strong> Control how and when we contact you
              </li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">Ralph Application Data</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              For data within your Ralph deployment, you have complete control as the data
              controller. You can manage user access, data retention, and deletion according to your
              organization's policies.
            </p>

            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a
                href="mailto:privacy@beneficious.com"
                class="text-accent hover:underline">privacy@beneficious.com</a
              >.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Updates to This Policy
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any
              material changes by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this policy.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              How We Share Information
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We may share your personal information in the following limited circumstances:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Service Providers:</strong> Trusted third parties who provide services on our
                behalf (hosting, analytics, customer support)
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law, court order, or to protect
                our rights and safety
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with mergers, acquisitions, or asset
                sales (with notice to you)
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>With Your Consent:</strong> Any other sharing will be done only with your explicit
                consent
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              <strong>We never sell your personal information to third parties.</strong>
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Data Retention
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We retain personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for
              which it was collected:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>
                <strong>Contact Information:</strong> Retained while you have an active business relationship
                with us
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Support Communications:</strong> Retained for a reasonable period to provide
                ongoing support
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> Some information may be retained longer to comply
                with legal obligations
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Ralph Application Data:</strong> You control all retention policies for data
                within your Ralph deployment
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              International Data Transfers
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              If we transfer your personal information outside your country of residence, we ensure
              adequate protection through:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>Appropriate contractual safeguards and security measures</li>
              <li>Compliance with applicable data protection laws</li>
              <li>Industry-standard encryption and security protocols</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              <strong>Remember:</strong> With Ralph's on-premise deployment model, your business data
              never crosses international boundaries unless you configure it to do so.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">
              Contact Us
            </h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your data
              rights, please contact us:
            </p>
            <div class="bg-card rounded-lg p-6 border border-neutral-700">
              <p>
                <strong>Privacy Inquiries:</strong><br />
                Email: <a
                  href="mailto:privacy@beneficious.com"
                  class="text-primary hover:text-accent transition-colors"
                  >privacy@beneficious.com</a
                >
              </p>

              <p class="mt-4">
                <strong>General Inquiries:</strong><br />
                Email: <a
                  href="mailto:info@beneficious.com"
                  class="text-primary hover:text-accent transition-colors">info@beneficious.com</a
                >
              </p>

              <p class="mt-4"><strong>Company:</strong> Beneficious</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We will respond to privacy-related inquiries within 30 days of receipt.
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Section>
  </main>
</SubpageLayout>

<style>
  /* Professional legal document styling */
  strong {
    @apply font-medium text-primary;
  }

  /* Section numbering and hierarchy */
  section h2 {
    @apply uppercase tracking-wide text-base;
  }

  /* Professional list styling */
  ul li {
    @apply leading-relaxed;
  }

  /* Emphasis styling for legal text */
  section p strong,
  section li strong {
    @apply font-semibold;
  }

  /* Contact info card */
  section:last-child div {
    @apply shadow-sm;
  }

  /* Important notices */
  p:has(strong:first-child) {
    @apply mt-6 p-4 bg-card/50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-accent/30;
  }
</style>
